September 15-17, 1992
Northeastern University
Burlington, Massachusetts, USA

     В сентябре состоится третий форум по обратной инженерии. Его прово-
дит Boston Computer Society's CASE SIG, Washington University CSDP  [St.
Louis],  International  Workshop  on  CASE (IWCASE), Software Management
News.
     При этом обратную инженерию американцы определяют как "an  evolving
collection  of  methods  and  technologies  to salvage an organization's
software  asset   through   automated  support   for   the  examination,
evaluation, documentation,  and renovation  of existing  software. It is
the  software  industry's  solution  to  the  growing mountain of legacy
systems that form a  maintenance backlog which, for  many organizations,
is stealing precious resources away from new development needed to  meet
changing  business  requirements.  Re-engineering  is the combination of
reverse engineering and redevelopment".
     Программа включает более двадцати докладов. С вступительным  словом
к  участникам  обратится  Николай  Звягинцев (Software Management News).
